Rory McIlroy Takes Eight-Shot Lead After Third Round at U.S. Open Golf

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-06-18T22:53:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-18/rory-mcilroy-reaches-a-record-14-under-par-in-3rd-round-at-u-s-open-golf.html
Rory McIlroy birdied the 14th hole
to advance to 14-under par at the  U.S. Open , the lowest score in
relation to par ever achieved at the major  golf tournament .  Jason Day and  Lee Westwood  are tied for second place at 5-
under par after rounds of 65 today at Congressional Country Club
in Bethesda,  Maryland . Y.E. Yang is also 5-under.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
